4.2 VISUALIZING SPATIAL TRANSFORMATION
To better understand the spatial transformation applied to the original images, we visualize the optimized transformation Ô¨Çow for different datasets, respectively. Figure 5 visualizes a transformation on an MNIST instance, where the digit ‚Äú0‚Äù is misclassiÔ¨Åed as ‚Äú2.‚Äù We can see that the adjacent Ô¨Çows move in a similar direction in order to generate smooth results.

