Figure 9: CAM attention visualization for ImageNet inception_v3 model. Column 1 shows the CAM map corresponding to the original image. Column 2-4 show the adversarial examples generated by different methods. The visualizations are drawn for Row 1: inception_v3 model; Row 2: (robust) adversarial trained inception_v3 model. (a) and (e)-(g) are labeled as the ground truth ‚Äúcinema‚Äù, while (b)-(d) and (h) are labeled as the adversarial target ‚Äúmissile.‚Äù

We also analyze the attack success rate of these examples under existing defense methods and demonstrate they are harder to defend against, which opens new directions for developing more robust defense algorithms. Finally, we visualize the attention regions of DNNs on our adversarial examples to better understand this new attack.
